{"workflow_number":65,"workflow_id":"derm-urticaria","title":"Urticaria","specialty":"Dermatology","diagnosis":"Acute urticaria","research_status":"partial_source_support","research_status_label":"Partial source support","uae_applicability":"No exact UAE urticaria guideline was identified; international guidance requires UAE clinician review.","uae_findings":[{"finding_type":"partial_applicability","evidence_basis":"Structured source status remains partial_exact_source_verified."}],"source_references":[{"source_resolves":true,"source_id":"eaaci-urticaria-guideline-2022","title":"The international EAACI/GA²LEN/EuroGuiDerm/APAAACI guideline for the definition, classification, diagnosis, and management of urticaria","issuing_organisation":"EAACI / GA²LEN / EuroGuiDerm / APAAACI","official_url":"https://eaaci.org/guidelines-position-papers/the-international-eaaci-ga%C2%B2len-euroguiderm-apaaaci-guideline-for-the-definition-classification-diagnosis-and-management-of-urticaria/","jurisdiction":"International specialty guidance","sections":[{"section_id":"eaaci-urticaria-2022-definition","heading":"Official abstract: definition and presentation","locator":"official page lines 99–103","evidence_summary":"Defines urticaria as a mast-cell-driven disease presenting with wheals, angioedema, or both and distinguishes acute and chronic forms."},{"section_id":"eaaci-urticaria-2022-impact-scope","heading":"Official abstract: impact and scope","locator":"official page lines 99–103","evidence_summary":"States that chronic spontaneous or inducible urticaria can impair quality of life and work or school performance and that the guideline covers classification, diagnosis, and management."}]},{"source_resolves":true,"source_id":"rcuk-anaphylaxis-2021","title":"Emergency treatment of anaphylaxis: Guidelines for healthcare providers","issuing_organisation":"Resuscitation Council UK","official_url":"https://www.resus.org.uk/sites/default/files/2021-05/Emergency%20Treatment%20of%20Anaphylaxi